2.  National  (individual;  energy  efficiency  technology  experts,  renewable  energy 
technology  experts,  water  technology  experts,  and  other  climate  technology 
experts,  as  required,  project  coordinator,  project  assistant;  100–120  person-
months) 

8.  The experts will 
(i)  coordinate work under the subproject; 
(ii)  provide  inputs  such  as  research  and  analysis,  data  collection,  draft  note 
preparation, briefs and progress reports, meeting materials, discussion minutes 
and summaries, outreach documents, and responses to queries; 
(iii)  facilitate the recruitment, engagement, and mobilization of consultants of firms 
and individuals, and management of payments; 
(iv)  assist  in  preparation  of  overall  work  plan  and  budget  and monitoring  of TA 
implementation; and 
(v)  create and manage TA database and records. 

D.  Subproject D: Demonstration of an Assisted Broker Model for Transfer of Low 
Carbon Technologies to Asia and Pacific 

1.  International (firms and individual; project implementation, operation, and design 
specialists; 280–300 person-months) 

9.  The experts will 
(i)  prepare the procedures and operation plans for the demonstration of the assisted 
broker model for technology transfer; 
(ii)  identify business opportunities for climate technologies; 
(iii)  develop business plans for buyers during negotiations, which will be the basis for 
recovering the cost of technology from product sales; 
(iv)  identify technology holders and licensing issues, landscape technologies and 
markets, including technology holders and potential buyers; 
(v)  monitor and evaluate technologies and technology holders; 
(vi)  conduct consultation exercises with technology holders and seekers on design; 
(vii)  provide  prioritized  markets  perspective  during  the  design  of  operational 
procedure and business plan; 
(viii)  provide inputs on intellectual property protection issues; 
(ix)  conduct a legal review of the operational and business plans; 
(x)  manage documentation, data, and financial management activities; 
(xi)  oversee technology transfer operations using the assisted broker model; 
(xii)  perform licensing and marketing activities, promote the assisted broker model in 
different forums, and establish partnerships with other similar efforts; 
(xiii)  evaluate the business opportunities for technologies, with technical advice from 
experts; 
(xiv)  draft  business  plans  for  buyers  during  negotiations,  which  will  the  basis  for 
recovering the cost of technology from product sales; 
(xv)  review and finalize the list of existing and potential intellectual property brokers; 
(xvi)  select technologies and countries and set up organizational structure; 
(xvii)  assist ADB and the operator in carrying out a midterm review and final report and 
provide inputs on developing the next phase of activities; 
(xviii)  provide inputs on latest climate change issues related to technology transfer, and 
discussions within and beyond the United Nations Framework Convention on 
Climate Change;

16  Appendix 3 
(xix)  assess the potential impact of low-carbon technologies in reducing greenhouse 
gas emissions in participating countries, review the climate change plans and 
policies of DMCs, provide inputs during selection of countries and technologies, 
and provide inputs on host government needs and priorities; 
(xx)  review and assist the operator in identifying and contacting LCT holders; 
(xxi)  provide inputs to the operator in selecting the technology area to be chosen first 
for the demonstration phase; 
(xxii)  assess  the  appropriate  institutional  and  organizational  setup  and  human 
resources for the demonstration phase and full-fledged operation of the assisted 
broker model; and 
(xxiii)  review intellectual property-related organizations and the procedures in countries 
where the low-carbon technologies have been developed and where they will be 
used. 

E.  Subproject E: Project Management  

1.  National (individual; project coordinator, project assistant; 60–70 person-months) 

10.  The experts will 
(i)  support coordination and integration between the TA and the other components 
of  the  Pilot  Asia-Pacific  Climate  Technology  Network  and  Finance  Center, 
specifically those that will be implemented by the United Nations Environment 
Programme (UNEP); 
(ii)  coordinate activities of TA subprojects, ensuring their linkages at national level;  
(iii)  assist other subproject teams in coordination and liaison activities; 
(iv)  prepare  and update the TA overall work plan and budget; 
(v)  organize  and  participate  in  meetings  (e.g.,  steering  committee  meetings), 
workshops,  and  training,  and  provide  assistance  in  report  and  proceeding 
preparation; 
(vi)  create and manage project database and records; 
(vii)  prepare progress reports, briefing notes, correspondence, and other documents 
that may be required by ADB and partners;  
(viii)  conduct dissemination and outreach activities; and 
(ix)  review  the  scope  and  modality  of  the  pilot  finance  center  and  make 
recommendations for its future.
